column3: Our Information Visualization students participated and won the Stockholm Digital Care competition in the Green Hackathon. Congratulations!!!

We visit Speakasso, our 2015 information visualization student project and C Awards winner for Public Magnet. Speakasso aesthetically visualizes speech patterns.
For more information: http://www.csc.kth.se/~acvds/info_vis/speakasso/

We are remembering our student project Skylike, a visualization of your social reading networks as constellations in the night sky.
More info: http://www.skylike.me/

Mockstar is a gesture-based interactive crowd simulator to train the rockstars of tomorrow! It is a project in the Multimodal Interaction course at KTH Royal Institute of Technology by Victor Larsson, Louise Wikstén, Joel Ekman and Petriina Piuhola.

We are visiting our C Awards 2014 winner explr.fm, a map visualizing your playlist's countries of origin. Have a great weekend!
More info and live application: http://explr.fm/
Professor Mattias Höjer inviting our Information Visualization students to participate in the Green Hackathon in Stockholm between February 12 and 13. We are looking forward to great projects!

We are very proud to announce that KTH's first MOOC was partially filmed and supported by the Visualization Studio VIC!! The Massive Open Online Course on Human Space Flight starts on April 18. Sing up! We already have.

Advanced Graphics and Interaction project Starshooter trains wheelchair pan and tilt control through a firing cannon game. Learn more at: http://starshooter.kspri.se/
A great start to 2016!
Happy New Year! May 2016 be filled with happy and rewarding days.
It was a year of extraordinary visits and big developments at KTH. Take a look back at some of our university's highlights from 2015. http://bit.ly/1mQSVBu
Happy holidays from all of us at KTH!

Enjoy the festivities in peace with your loved ones and have a great 2016! This is a view of the universe at its grandest scale. Every dot is a galactic-sized object or quasar. We are looking at the universe billions of years into the past and billions of light light years away. The dark bands are regions occluded by the plane of the Milky Way. The view is powered by Visualization Studio VIC and Uniview. For a video tour of the universe including this view, please visit: https://www.facebook.com/VisualizationStudio/videos/1079237302139697/

YAAAAY! We hit 1000 likes just in time for the holidays. Enjoy this time in peace with your loved ones! We celebrate this milestone with a short tour of the universe guided by our Associate Profesor Mario Romero and powered by our 4K screen running Uniview. Thank you for a wonderful 2015! 

We thank Ronald Bernette for the production of this video.
Björn highlighting exoplanets within 30 parsecs.
Our students in co-operative IT-design and business development showcasing their projects to clients from COOP, KI/KS and DS. Very impressive results!
Master thesis work by Terese Nothnagel in embodied visualization.
We were honored with visits from KTH Executive School and our KTH Alumni Network.
Our Computer Game Design students present their wonderful final projects! Videos and more information coming soon! For the course page, please visit: https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2650/

Preparing for tomorrow's event with Road2Science. More Info: https://www.road2science.se/events/6
We could try to describe what it feels like to have the studio serve so many people in so many ways at once (lecture, design, programming, group projects, and demos) but a picture will say it better!

The Advanced Graphics and Interaction students hosted our Visualization Studio VIC's 2015 Open House. We had a large crowd enjoying a dozen projects with smiles and cheers. Thank you for participating and we'll see you next year! For more information, please visit: https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-open-house/

World, we present to you our hot-off-the-press student project ColorSplat! It is an augmented virtuality game where a physical ball turns into a virtual blob of paint with which you aim at moving targets. Just one of our nine new projects which we will present at our Open House tomorrow at 15:00 - 19:00. Please join us! The event is free and open to all ages. https://www.facebook.com/events/658200147655412/

World, we present to you our brand new project Spinnulator! It is a spinning simulator with Kinect tracking of the biker's skeleton, just one of the nine new projects we will be showing at our Open House on Friday, 3-7PM! Join us! It is free and open to everyone of all ages.
We are so ready to show you the future of interactive graphics on Friday, at our Open House 3-7PM
We say live long and prosper to our magical studio engineer Henrik as he joins the most exciting job user testing Paradox Interactive titles!
Tommy Palm from Resolution Games capturing so much attention at our Game Design course. More info: http://www.resolutiongames.com/

Multimodal interaction and interfaces students 2015 test YA3 as part of the lecture on mixed realities and tracking and wall and surface interaction. More info: http://ya3.philipshield.com/

Our friends at Visual Arena in Lindholmen are hosting a great visualization conference soon - Visual Forum 2015 on November 18. Get inspired, deepen your knowledge and make new connections with speakers, exhibitors and conference participants. Topics include augmented reality, virtual reality, autonomous systems, simulation, smart cities, gaming, connectivity and more. Visual Forum website and registration: http://visualforum.lindholmen.se/en

We are so looking forward to experience the out-of-this-world projects that our brand new students in Multimodal Interaction and Interfaces 2015 will create in the next few months!!! Welcome to our studio students!
Our spin off start up Flying Colors 3D joined us on Saturday at Comic Con Stockholm and shared fun moments with 3D artists and apprentices of all ages!
Advanced Graphics and Interaction 2015 students returning home from Comic Con Stockholm. Welcome!

Students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction at KTH Royal Institute of Technology present their course projects at Comic Con Stockholm as part of their course examination. For more information, please visit:
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/
Our report from Saturday at Comic Con Stockholm: our students have not stopped exhibiting for a single minute since 10:00 and people are having a great time!

Our Padawan 101 students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm over the weekend at Friends Arena. Join us!
Padawan 101 is an immersive training program for young jedis where the learners battle training spheres eager to shoot and shock them. The experience combines accelerometer and gyroscope sensing on the phone to orient a light saber virtually attached to it, a skeleton tracked by a Microsoft Kinect that allows the young jedi to move the sword around and the virtual reality experience of the Oculus Rift augmented with sound effects.
For more information, please visit:
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/
Our first report from the ground: Advanced graphics and interaction very much on-demand

Our Blopper students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm starting today, Friday, and over the weekend at Friends Arena. Join us!
Blopper is a full-body immersion into a game of balloon popping. It combines a Microsoft Kinect with a Google Cardboard and an Android Samsung.
For more information, please visit:
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

Our Shmooning students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm starting tomorrow Friday and over the weekend at Friends Arena. Join us!
Shmooning is the virtual reality experience of an astronaut struggling to return to moonbase battling through paratrooping martians. It combines Wii-mote control with Oculus Rift immersion. 
For more information, please visit: 
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

Our Shmooning students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm this starting tomorrow Friday and over the weekend at Friends Arena. Join us!
Shmooning is the virtual reality experience of an astronaut returning to moon base battling through a field of paratrooping martians. It connects Wii-mote controls with Oculus Rift.
For more information, please visit: 
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/
Look, look! Our space is already built and waiting for our installation. It is the long one in the center with the three tall walls at a 45 degree angle.

Our BRARWL students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm this weekend at Friends Arena. Join us!

BRARWL is a multiplayer fighting game in augmented reality for mobile devices. By looking on the game board through the camera on the device, the player controls a fighter with an on-screen gamepad.
For more information, please visit: 
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

Our BRARWL students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm this weekend at Friends Arena. Join us!

BRARWL is a multiplayer fighting game in augmented reality for mobile devices. By looking on the game board through the camera on the device, the player can control the character with an on-screen gamepad.
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

The KTH Royal Institute of Technology Advanced Graphics and Interaction 2015 students and the Visualization Studio VIC invite you to experience the future of interactive graphics through our students' six state of the art projects at Comic Con Stockholm in Friends Arena. For more information please visit: https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

Our BrARwl students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm this weekend at Friends Arena. Join us to get a glimpse into the future of mobile games!
BrARwl is an augmented reality game where multiple players use their phone's camera and screen to peek into a fantasy world of gladiators and control their champion to be the last standing. Join us, it's terribly fun and innovative! 
For more information, please visit: 
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

Our Teamtris students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm this weekend at Friends Arena. Join us!

Teamtris provides two orthogonal views of the same tower of blocks where two players rotate and translate the blocks communicating to collaboratively improve their score. It is a new mind bender of the old game of skill. 
For more information, please visit: 
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

Our Mad Sand students of Advanced Graphics and Interaction wait for you during Comic Con Stockholm this weekend at Friends Arena. Join us!

Mad Sand is an augmented-reality asymmetrical game for two people to drive a penguin over a changing landscape and collect as much candy as possible. It's fun and innovative! For more information, please visit: 
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

With just one week to go, we are very excited about showing you the advanced graphics and interaction projects at Comic Con Stockholm! Join us!

For more information on the projects, please visit: 
https://www.kth.se/social/course/DH2413/page/agi15-comic-con-gamex/

GIS students testing an embodied sculpting experience that includes stereoscopic first-person active projection with sound and haptic feedback. In other words, you see, hear, and feel that the model is physically in front of you.

GIS students exploring MadSand. That is, geographic information systems students are exploring an interactive and immersive augmented reality experience where the user modifies the geography of the game by literally digging into physical sand

Forma i Luften at Tekniska museet! People can sculpt a volume of air and see, hear, and feel what they are doing. It is accessible to people with mobility, hearing, and seeing impairments and it is sized for children. If you stop by Stockholm's Tekniska Museet, please visit!
We're on the front page of KTH CSC's Numera newsletter! Yay!!!

We created the permanent museum exhibit Forma i luften, shaping the air, at the Museum of Science and Technology of Stockholm. People can sculpt a volume of air and see, hear, and feel what they are doing. It is accessible to people with mobility, hearing, and seeing impairments and it is sized for children. If you stop by Stockholm's Tekniska museet, please visit!
